last_episode_to_air.name: Summit Or Die
last_episode_to_air.overview: In the series finale, the last members of the expedition make a final exhausting push to the summit of Mt. Tocllaraju… but not everything goes as planned.

name: Ultimate Expedition
overview: Nine strangers are brought together to summit a 20,000-foot mountain in the Peruvian Andes. With each step, these novice climbers will push themselves to their limits and beyond.

episodes.name: We've All Got A Screw Loose
I Have To Climb Up That?
episodes.overview: The climbers push themselves to exhaustion, and they still have a vertical ice wall to climb. Gus runs into trouble while Nikki pushes herself beyond fatigue.

episodes.name: Hanging By A Wire
episodes.overview: When a series of ice bridges collapse up on the mountain trail, the team scrambles to learn crevasse rescue training. Pete’s body becomes cumbersome while Chuck shows signs of illness.

episodes.name: Running Out Of Air
episodes.overview: The team tackles their first mountain, Ishinca, but the weight of their gear quickly wears them down. Nikki looks to redeem herself while Chuck’s cough raises concerns.

episodes.name: Knockout Punch
episodes.overview: Mountaineering gets very real as the team attempts to summit the 18,000-foot Mount Ishinca. Pete tests his limits while Chuck shows that he has the heart of a fighter.

episodes.name: The Trouble With Steve-O
episodes.overview: The team learns that getting down from the summit is just as hard as getting up, and an old injury comes back to haunt Steve-O.

episodes.name: Ladder To Hell
episodes.overview: Summit Day. The group attempts their ultimate goal, to reach the peak of Mt. Tocllaraju. Steve-O has a plan while Chachi battles the extreme cold.

episodes.name: Summit Or Die
episodes.overview: In the series finale, the last members of the expedition make a final exhausting push to the summit of Mt. Tocllaraju… but not everything goes as planned.
